EDF Terminates Involvement in Carbon Project in Honduras

-- B y   C a t h e r i n e   A i r l i e
-- 
2011-04-14T13:36:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/edf-ends-contract-with-co2-project-linked-to-human-rights-abuses.html
The trading unit of Electricite de
France SA said it will terminate its involvement in a project to
receive credits under the United Nation’s Clean Development
Mechanism for the Aguan biogas project in  Honduras .  “We take a responsible appraoch to our CDM portfolio,”
said John Rittenhouse, chief executive officer at EDF Trading.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Catherine Airlie in London at 
